Some thirty years later we are still trying to decipher facts and figgures about our southeast asian venture.I would venture to say every war has its casulties. What stats don't state is the mood of the country at the time, or how anyone can relate to  someone elses  age group at his present age.  I tend to disagree with the previous statement about the veteran  recieving 18% higher earnings.Historically, the absent veteran misses opportunity that the civilian takes advantage of. I also tend to believe in strong commaraderi. I made some lifelong friends from that era that we still keep in contact with,of course we don't agree on any of our stories, but in time i'm sure they will see it my way.I served south of Ben Hoa in 69 at age 21. I'm 48 now  and have come to realize that life goes on. I have become very active in politics, with life's lessons if enough of us get involved just mabe we can make a difference .
<p><code>-- dmc@rmi.net  (L.C. Army) </code><p>


